      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear-elastic model with frictional contact at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces; material nonlinearity captured via bilinear isotropic hardening for titanium alloy.",
      "rationale": "The chosen model form — continuum FEA with bilinear hardening and frictional contact — is well-established for metallic spinal implant constructs. Literature precedent (Goel, Rohlmann, FDA bench-to-FEA studies) supports this formulation. Sensitivity studies confirm that contact friction coefficient variation (0.2–0.4) produces <3% QoI change. Required level 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
