      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certified coupon testing of the same Ti-6Al-4V ELI heat lot used for the test constructs; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of production screws.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus (1.1 GPa) derived from tensile testing of three coupons from the same material heat lot. CMM measurements of screw geometry (thread profile, core diameter) used directly in CAD reconstruction. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo; QoI sensitivity to E is <1.5%. Required level 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥6 constructs tested; samples drawn from production lot with documented traceability; coefficient of variation <15% for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes). All samples from the same production lot with full traceability documentation. CV for stiffness = 4.2%, yield force = 5.8%, force at 40 mm = 6.1%. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate in-vivo loading environment across at least two load cases; environmental controls (temperature, humidity) documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed strictly under ASTM F1717 single-load-case protocol (compression-bending only). While this is the regulatory standard, it represents a single test condition and does not capture torsion or lateral bending scenarios relevant to in-vivo use. Temperature and humidity controlled and documented. Achieved level 2 is below the required level 3 for this medium-risk COU; this gap is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory context of the ASTM F1717 submission."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA input parameters (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to experimental test configuration; traceability documented.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions mirror the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry exactly. Screw insertion torque and set-screw torque applied in FEA as pre-load equivalent to experimental protocol. Material properties sourced from same lot as test samples. Full traceability matrix maps each FEA input to its experimental counterpart. Required level 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percentage difference <10%.",
      "rationale": "E/uval values: stiffness = 0.82, yield force = 1.14, force at 40 mm = 1.31. All below the 1.96 threshold. Percentage differences: stiffness 3.2%, yield force 4.1%, force at 40 mm 6.7%. All within 10% acceptance criterion. Comparison performed against pooled experimental mean and combined uncertainty from both laboratories. Required level 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Qualitative assessment of clinical and regulatory relevance of selected QoIs to the intended use of the model.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs — construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement — are the standard outputs specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly relevant to the regulatory submission context. Construct stiffness characterises load-sharing behaviour; yield force indicates onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm displacement captures post-yield structural integrity. A qualitative assessment by the modelling team and the reviewing regulatory scientist confirms that these QoIs adequately represent the biomechanical performance attributes relevant to patient safety for this device class. No quantitative level mapping was applied to this factor, as the relevance determination was made through structured expert elicitation and documented review rather than through the standard gradation rubric; the consensus finding is that the QoIs are fully appropriate for the COU."
    },
